&lt;br /&gt;
A whimsical adventure awaits you at Big Bear&amp;#39;s Hobbit House! This historic cabin built in 1928 offers a unique interior with little doors and hidden stairs between rooms, and a secret passage awaits discovery. This home combines the best of vintage Big Bear with modern amenities, showcasing big screen TVs against stained glass windows.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A programmable ceiling fan keeps the home cool in the summer, and a traditional cabin kitchen with a claw-foot bathtub in the adjacent bathroom are a beautiful reminder that this home has been hosting guests for almost 100 years.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This cabin is near just about everything. Snow Summit and Bear Mountain Ski Resorts each a quick drive away for wintertime fun, and the lake is a few moments to the north. Enjoy hiking and biking trails and swimming at Meadow Park in the summertime or the shops and restaurants of the village year-round. There are a few eateries a couple blocks north of the home.&lt;br /&gt;
