property.description:
&lt;strong&gt;Play Big Bear &amp;ndash; Relaxing Bear City Family Retreat | Pool Table | Foosball | Arcade Games&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Welcome to your dream mountain escape here at Play Big Bear! This beautifully renovated and cozy Bear City home offers everything you need to enjoy relaxing moments and lifelong memories together beneath soaring pine trees and star-filled skies any time of the year. Hop in the car and you&amp;rsquo;ll be within ten minutes of local ski resorts, marinas, and Village shops&amp;mdash;this cottage truly puts the best of Big Bear right at your fingertips.&lt;br /&gt;
Enter the inviting living room, where gorgeous hardwood floors, freshly painted walls, and large windows welcome in natural light and snowy mountain views. Snuggle up on the cozy couch and warm up by the toasty fireplace while watching a movie on the flat-screen TV, or challenge your group to a friendly game on the foosball table. The open floor plan flows seamlessly into the dining area and fully equipped kitchen, where the chef of your group can prepare home-cooked meals or slope-side snacks with ease. Oak cabinetry is stocked with cookware and utensils, while stainless-steel appliances and a dishwasher make cleanup a breeze. Gather around the formal dining table and enjoy your meals together while taking in the forested views outside.&lt;br /&gt;
This single-level home offers easy access to all three sleeping quarters and both modern bathrooms, ensuring comfort and convenience for the whole group. Fresh linens and bath towels are provided upon arrival so you can settle in and enjoy a restful night after a full day of mountain adventures.&lt;br /&gt;
Step outside and enjoy the great outdoors on the open, forested property. The small patio and sun deck are equipped with a propane BBQ, perfect for grilling up dinner in the evenings and relaxing under the mountain sky. This mountain home is conveniently located near a main intersection in Bear City. While this offers easy access to local attractions and main roads, it also means that some road noise is to be expected, especially during peak travel times, weekends, and winter season. Guests who are sensitive to noise may wish to plan accordingly.&lt;br /&gt;
Come experience your home away from home in the mountains here at Play Big Bear!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
