Pinewood Haus ~ Beautiful &amp;amp; Convenient 1960s Cabin w/ Wood Stove, near Skiing &amp;amp; Lake Attractions&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Pinewood Haus is a modified A-frame, named the Li&amp;rsquo;l Cabin in the Woods during the infancy of Big Bear&amp;rsquo;s evolution to a ski town. Built in 1968, this home remains an architectural icon of 1960s Big Bear and a peaceful, all-seasons mountain retreat for friends and family alike.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Ideally located on a quiet cul-de-sac in the desirable Fox Farm area, within minutes of Big Bear&amp;rsquo;s ski resorts and village, Pinewood Haus is central to all of Big Bear&amp;rsquo;s attractions and conveniences while offering the blissful feeling of seclusion. Easy access to local routes helps you avoid peak season traffic.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Pinewood Haus feels warm and charming, bringing you back to days gone by. But don&amp;rsquo;t let the nostalgia fool you - this well-maintained cabin is cute, comfortable, and full of modern conveniences. Enjoy high ceilings, plentiful natural light throughout, a corner fireplace to set the cozy mountain mood, and central heating to keep you thoroughly toasty. Mountain breezes whispering through the pines cool the house in summertime.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Settle into that warm cabin feeling by streaming your favorite shows on the Smart TV or utilizing the complimentary Wi-Fi. Other accommodations include a handy washer/dryer located off the hallway from the vintage kitchen, which is fully appointed with appliances, pots, pans, utensils, coffee makers (drip and French press), a kettle, and a grinder. The private bedroom on the main level features a queen-size bed, while the open and airy loft offers two full beds. The retro living room has full-size sleeper sofa. The bathroom is simple and features a large walk-in shower.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Outside, commune with nature by spending time on the quaint wood decks. The front deck faces the quiet neighboring homes, with flat easy access off the cul-de-sac (there are no arduous driveways to get to Pinewood Haus - a bonus in the winter months). The back faces the pines in the 12,600-square-foot open lot.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Sleeping Arrangements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Bedroom 1: Queen Bed, Streaming TV- Downstairs Entry Level&lt;br /&gt;
Loft/Bedroom 2: Two Double Beds, Streaming TV- Upstairs 2nd Level&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Bathroom Arrangements:&lt;br /&gt;
Hallway Full Bath- Downstairs Entry Level&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
~Sleeps 6&lt;br /&gt;
~2 Car Driveway Parking&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
~NO PETS ALLOWED&lt;br /&gt;
~960 Square Feet&lt;br /&gt;
~County Permit #:&amp;nbsp;CESTRP-2020-01177&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;

