property.description:
Bristlecone Cottage ~ Ideally Located Cabin Near Skiing &amp;amp; Hiking w/ Wood Stove &amp;amp; Full Kitchen&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Indulge in that romantic escape or getaway with friends and make this cabin your home base for a little while in Big Bear. With rustic touches and warm wood accents, you&amp;#39;ll feel like you&amp;#39;re in your own private oasis while being mere minutes from all of the best attractions.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Cold winter nights will be well spent with a warm mug of hot cocoa by the wood stove. The chef of the group will love hopping into the full kitchen to prepare tasty, home-cooked meals. Come summer, you can step out onto the furnished deck and enjoy a cocktail in the fresh mountain air as you reminisce about the day&amp;#39;s events. Entertainment won&amp;#39;t be a problem when the stars come out either, as the flatscreen TV and free Wi-Fi can facilitate movie nights with ease.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This location couldn&amp;#39;t get any better when it comes to outdoor activity. The skiers of the group will be in paradise knowing that Bear Mountain Ski Resort and Big Bear Mountain Resort are both within two miles. If a leisurely hike or bike ride is on the agenda, walk two blocks to the Bristlecone Trail and enjoy the scenery that this area is known for. When the warmer times of year come around, Big Bear Lake is just three miles north, where you can spend a day boating, fishing, or swimming in beautiful blue water. Not to mention, Moonridge Coffee Company and Dank Donuts are within walking distance to fuel you up for a day on the slopes.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Sleeping Arrangements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Bedroom: Queen Bed&lt;br /&gt;
Living Room: Futon Bed&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Bathroom Arrangements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Hallway 3/4 Bath (Shower Only)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
~Sleeps 3&lt;br /&gt;
~1 Car Driveway Parking&lt;br /&gt;
~NO PETS ALLOWED&lt;br /&gt;
~588 Square Feet&lt;br /&gt;
