property.description:
&lt;strong&gt;Vista Sugarloaf ~Mountain getaway near town &amp;amp; skiing w/ gas grill &amp;amp; spacious deck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
There is no better place for an outdoorsy retreat than Big Bear Lake, so make your way to this amazing cabin and make the best mountain memories today. After long lake days or an afternoon on the slopes, cuddle up next to the wood-burning fireplace with a cup of hot cocoa or that new novel you have been meaning to get to.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
When guests build up an appetite, there will be no reason to head into town for a bite to eat with the full kitchen right at your fingertips featuring a gas range and all of the utensils needed to create gourmet meals. Plus, the private gas grill on the back deck will make whipping up a few burgers a breeze when everyone is craving a summer cookout in the fresh air!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
What&amp;#39;s nearby:&lt;br /&gt;
Sitting in the quiet neighborhood of Sugarloaf, you will feel like a local in no time. When you want to venture into town, make the quick three-mile drive to Big Bear proper or eight-mile drive into the heart of Big Bear Lake both offering eclectic shops, gear rental shops, restaurants, and grocery stores for all of your shopping needs. Come winter, the skiers of the group will be glad to know that Snow Summit Ski Resort is just over seven miles from home base and Bear Mountain Ski Resort is seven-and-a-half miles. Not to mention, Big Bear Lake will be the summer hit for fishing, boating, paddleboarding, and swimming!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Sleeping Arrangements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Bedroom 1: Queen Bed&lt;br /&gt;
Bedroom 2: Queen Bed + Twin/Twin Bunk&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Bathroom Arrangements:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Hallway Full Bath&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
~Sleeps 6&lt;br /&gt;
~3 Car Driveway Parking&lt;br /&gt;
~NO Pets&lt;br /&gt;
~902 Square Feet&lt;br /&gt;
~County Permit #:&amp;nbsp;CESTRP-2020-01382

